<h1>Sallie Boyce</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://spra.co/now/">spra.co/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Cotswolds

United Kingdom
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Founder of The Startup PR Academy <<a href="http://spra.co/>">http://spra.co/></a> & Communica PR <<a href="http://communicapr.com/>">http://communicapr.com/></a>
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I support entrepreneurs on their journey to increase the visibility + credibility of their brand through targeted media exposure.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I believe every entrepreneurs should know how to achieve press coverage. Whether it’s for their business, for them or for their pet project.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Always be on a mission. Don’t just promote your widget. Be for something.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Business for Punks <<a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/Business-Punks-Break-Rules-BrewDog-ebook/dp/B00XBC8BFA>">http://www.amazon.co.uk/Business-Punks-Break-Rules-BrewDog-ebook/dp/B00XBC8BFA></a> by James Watt
</p>

